T1  - Central Americans in Los Angeles: Background, language, education.
A1  - Penalosa, Fernando

Y1  - 1986//
N2  - Discusses the background, characteristics, and experience of Central American immigration to the US. The social life and customs, the multilingual environment in the old and new homes, and the difficulties surrounding schooling in the US are described. Problems faced by the immigrants involve employment, health care, welfare, housing, and interethnic relations. It is noted that being refugees from death and violence in their homeland, the most frequent psychological problems among immigrants involve a sense of loss and separation that is manifested in depression, anxiety, and confusion. Children especially may suffer posttraumatic stress disorder (PTSD) syndrome from having suppressed so much emotion in the struggle to survive. (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2021 APA, all rights reserved)
