T1  - Reflections on the psychoanalytic process, with special emphasis on child analysis and self-analysis.
A1  - Weiss, Samuel

Y1  - 1981//
N2  - Explores the importance of negative transference, its definitions and distinctions, and its role in the treatment of adolescent and juvenile delinquents. Negative and violent feelings will emerge in the treatment of adolescents, especially if the underlying psychopathology is borderline or narcissistic. Negative transference does not indicate that treatment cannot be successful. It must be confronted and interpreted, and it must not be permitted to split off or be displaced. The supportive environment of a therapeutic hospital milieu is suggested. It is proposed that hostility in treatment is not an evil to be eliminated, but rather an aspect of the patient's psychopathology that must be dealt with as are other feelings and transferences. (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2021 APA, all rights reserved)
