T1  - Problems of Southeast Asian children in a refugee camp.
T3  - American Journal of Insanity
A1  - Harding, Richard K
A1  - Looney, John G

Y1  - 1977//
N2  - Discusses the efforts made to meet the mental health needs of Vietnamese children and their families in a large US refugee camp. Many of the children received strong emotional support from the multigenerational Vietnamese families, and they adapted well to the new environment. However, children separated from their families demonstrated increased emotional vulnerability, and foster placement of children without families presented a serious problem. It is suggested that Americans' national commitment to these refugees may have ended when they (the refugees) left the confines of the refugee camp. (19 ref) (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2021 APA, all rights reserved)
