T1  - Trauma and the delinquent.
A1  - Marohn, Richard C

Y1  - 1974//
N2  - Demonstrates in 7 case studies of hospitalized delinquents that violent behavior is a diffuse discharge phenomenon, the result of the psychic apparatus being flooded with internal stimulation and the stimulus barrier being breached. These traumatic states approximate metapsychologically the psycho-economic imbalance of Freud's actual neurosis, and resemble clinically transient psychosis. Such problems may readily arise in dealing with adolescents whose ego capacities are taxed, especially those with ego deficits, such as delinquents. Treatment necessitates a milieu that is safe, where staff members function as auxiliary egos and stimulus barriers, much as a competent mother does for her infant. (27 ref) (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2021 APA, all rights reserved)
