T1  - Management of psychosomatic disorder.
A1  - Leigh, Denis

Y1  - 1968//
N2  - Distinguishes between psychosomatic medicine and disorders stressing the relationship between psychosocial disturbance and the occurrence of the illness. The vulnerability of certain individuals to the stresses of life changes is an important causative factor of psychosomatic disorders. "The forms the illnesses take are dictated by stock, genetic, constitutional, and environmental factors." The fact that a perceptive family doctor can exercise a preventive role is emphasized. The general setting, anxiety, environment, and drugs are involved in the development and treatment of the illness. Management is discussed in relation to the specific illness (asthma, migraine, peptic ulcer, and childhood disturbances). (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2021 APA, all rights reserved)
