N2  - AS MEASURED BY RATES OF 1ST ADMISSIONS, WHITE MIGRANTS HAVE A SIGNIFICANTLY HIGHER INCIDENCE OF MENTAL ILLNESS THAN DO WHITE NONMIGRANTS. EXCLUDING PUERTO RICANS, THE RATE OF 1ST ADMISSIONS/100,000 WHITE POPULATION AGE 15 YR. AND OVER IN NEW YORK STATE, 1960-1961, WAS 241.6 FOR MIGRANTS AND 163.3 FOR NONMIGRANTS. MIGRANTS ALSO HAD HIGHER RATES OF 1ST ADMISSIONS WITH SCHIZOPHRENIA THAN NONMIGRANTS. OTHER STUDIES SUPPORTING THE ENVIRONMENTAL FACTOR INTERPRETATION ARE MENTIONED. IT IS CONCLUDED THAT "MIGRATION, WHEN ASSOCIATED WITH MINORITY STATUS, IS CHARACTERIZED BY A DEGREE OF INSECURITY WHICH MAY HAVE AS A CONSEQUENCE A HIGHER INCIDENCE OF MENTAL DISORDER." (16 REF.) (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2021 APA, all rights reserved)
