N2  - Examination of 25 displaced children, whose ages averaged between 15 and 20 revealed a dissatisfaction with foster home placement. Their complaints regarding food, what they expected of the social agency, and job placement were on an unrealistic basis. Various symptoms are discussed which indicate extreme dependency and inability to accept mother's death. The approach for treatment is to provide an environment with objective understanding to guarantee the "acting out" of all problems, thereby directing them toward the necessary adjustment. (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2021 APA, all rights reserved)
